<HEADLINE> Emanating Wins After Long Layoff  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- After seven months of inactivity, Emanating
returned to competition in fine fettle, drawing away through the
final furlong to post a 1\-length victory over Luricon in Belmont
Park's Sunday feature, a $48,000 turf allowance for fillies and
mares 3 and older.
</P>
<P>
   It was another neck back in the field of six to Bridal Glow.
Eze, the favorite, trailed to the far turn and then rallied only
mildly to be fourth.
</P>
<P>
   Ridden by Mike Smith and carrying 120 pounds, Emanating covered
1[ miles in 1:49:1 on the firm inner turf course to earn $28,800
for Cynthia Phipps. It was the fourth win in 13 career starts for
the 4-year-old filly by Cox's Ridge from the Majest Light mare,
Lead Kindly Light.
</P>
<P>
   The winner returned $5.80, $3.70 and $3.20. Luricon paid $4.10
and $4.20, while Bridal Glow was $3.90 to show.
</P>
