<HEADLINE> Royals 7, Pirates 5, 11 Innings  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   PITTSBURGH (AP) -- Dave McCarty's two-run double capped a
three-run 11th inning for Kansas City, and Jermaine Dye homered for
the third straight game as the Royals beat the Pittsburgh Pirates
7-5 on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   The Royals rallied to win after Jerry Spradlin gave up a
two-out, game-tying pinch-hit homer to Wil Cordero in the ninth
inning.
</P>
<P>
   Carlos Beltran doubled with one out in the 11th off Jason
Christiansen (1-4), just missing a home run by inches. After Joe
Randa was walked intentionally, Gregg Zaun to load the bases.
</P>
