<HEADLINE> Tigers 3, Cubs 2, 12 Innings  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   CHICAGO (AP) -- Shane Halter's bunt single with two outs in the
12th inning scored the winning run as the Detroit Tigers beat the
Chicago Cubs 3-2 on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   Bobby Higginson walked to lead off the 12th against Todd Van
Poppel (0-1). One out later, Higginson stole second and he advanced
to third on a groundout.
</P>
<P>
   With third baseman Willie Greene playing back, Halter dropped a
bunt down the third-base line to score the first run off Van Poppel
in 15 innings of relief.
</P>
<P>
   Matt Anderson (3-0) pitched two hitless innings for the win, and
Todd Jones pitched the 12th for his 16 save in 17 chances.
</P>
<P>
   Jon Lieber allowed two runs and five hits in nine innings, but
got a no-decision. He walked none and struck out 10 for his second
straight double-digit strikeout game.
</P>
<P>
   Lieber, who lost 1-0 to Greg Maddux and Atlanta his last start,
has allowed three runs and seven hits in his last 17 innings, but
is 0-1 in the two starts.
</P>
