<HEADLINE> Solvig Outduels Trip to Win Regret  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOUISVILLE, Ky. (AP) -- Solvig, ridden by Pat Day, took the lead
at the top of the stretch and outdueled Trip for a one-length
victory in the $168,450 Grade III Regret for 3-year-old fillies at
Churchill Downs on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   Winning for the first time since capturing the Tropical Park
Oaks on Jan. 1, the daughter of Caerlon covered 1 1-16 miles in
1:42.95 and paid $4, $2.40 and $2.20 as the even-money favorite in
the field of nine. Trip paid $2.80 and $2.60, while Miss Chief
finished another 2\ lengths back in third and paid $3.20 to show.
</P>
<P>
   Owned by the Revocable Trust of Bentley Smith and trained by
Carl Nafzger, Solvig earned $104,439 to boost her lifetime earnings
to $317,314. The victory was her second in four starts this year
and fifth in eight lifetime starts, all on turf.
</P>
<P>
   The track announced a record crowd -- 19,032 -- for a Sunday. The
attendance figure marked the fourth day-of-the-week record
established during this spring meet. The previous largest crowd for
a Sunday was 18,017, set on May 14.
</P>
</TEXT>
