<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-04 19:47 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Putin Neutral in US President Race  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MOSCOW (AP) -- Russian President Vladimir Putin isn't taking
sides in the U.S. presidential election of a successor to his
summit partner. He says the Russians are willing to go forward with
either Vice President Al Gore or Texas Gov. George W. Bush.
</P>
<P>
   ''We know that today, in the United States, there is a campaign
ongoing,'' he said Sunday at the summit-closing ceremony in the
Kremlin. ''We're familiar with the programs of the two main
candidates.''
</P>
<P>
   From that point, his remarks got cryptic, perhaps losing
something in the translation. Or perhaps demonstrating Putin's own
political skill, since he said nothing either Democrats or
Republicans could find objectionable.
</P>
<P>
   ''And if these programs are implemented,'' he went on, ''and
there it says, for instance, the necessity to positively improve
relations between Russia and the United States, the time that Mr.
Clinton is going to pass on to the next president, no matter who
gets to be president, we're willing to go forward with either one
of these approaches.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
