<HEADLINE> Senators Acquire Tampa Bay Goalie  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   KANATA, Ontario (AP) -- The Ottawa Senators acquired goaltender
Rich Parent from the Tampa Bay Lightning on Sunday for a
seventh-round pick in the 2000 NHL draft.
</P>
<P>
   Parent played in 14 games this season, posting a 2-7-1 record
and a 3.70 goals-against average. He was 20-14 with a 2.30
goals-against average with Detroit of the IHL.
</P>
<P>
   The Senators only have goaltender Patrick Lalime under contract
for next season. Tom Barrasso is an unrestricted free agent.
</P>
