Police arrested 41 people -- 35 of whom were among 200 who mobbed a bus
containing three OAS delegates and a driver, according to Staff Sgt. Dave
Rossell of the Windsor Police Service. Protesters chanted ''Shame! Shame!
Shame!'' and wagged their fingers at the police officers, who in turn rapped
nightsticks on riot shields to move the crowd back. Some demonstrators tried to
force their way into the area before police shut the gate, inciting the
demonstrators to throw bottles and debris.
