<HEADLINE> Astra Takes Gamely Breeders' Cup  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   INGLEWOOD, Calif. (AP) -- After five wins in six starts against
lesser competition, Astra beat even-money favorite Happyanunoit by
a half-length in Sunday's $240,950 Gamely Breeders' Cup Handicap at
Hollywood Park.
</P>
<P>
   Kent Desormeaux rallied the 4-year-old filly from fourth in the
field of five to overtake Happyanunoit within the final sixteenth
of a mile of the 1[-mile race. She was timed in 1:45 4-5.
</P>
<P>
   Tout Charmant finished third, four lengths behind Happyanunoit.
</P>
<P>
   Astra, whose biggest previous victory came in April's Grade III
Jenny Wiley Stakes at Keeneland, was the Gamely's fourth choice at
7-2 odds.
</P>
<P>
   Astra, who carried 117 pounds, paid $9.60 and $4.20. She won
$157,170, nearly doubling the bay filly's earnings, which moved to
$345,424.
</P>
<P>
   Happyanunoit, the 121-pound high weight, paid $3.20 to place.
There was no show wagering.
</P>
