<HEADLINE> UN human rights chief fears conference may reverse women's gains  </HEADLINE>
By EDITH M. LEDERER
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- On the eve of a U.N. conference to assess
progress toward equality of the sexes, the U.N. High Commissioner
for Human Rights accused some countries of trying to reverse the
gains won by women at a global gathering five years ago.
</P>
<P>
   Mary Robinson declined to name the countries, but Amnesty
International's Secretary-General Pierre Sane said Algeria, Libya,
